                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12846937" author="chrismattmann" created="Thu, 18 Mar 2010 14:40:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1! I&apos;ve ran into this issue myself, and the overhead IMHO is worth is for the ease of use...&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12847374" author="jukkaz" created="Fri, 19 Mar 2010 13:52:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;As of revision 925217 the AutoDetectParser wraps all incoming streams to BufferedInputStream regardless of whether they claim mark support or not. Resolving as fixed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12847509" author="d.de.wit" created="Fri, 19 Mar 2010 18:47:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I did not test it, and it might be a premature optimization, but wouldn&apos;t it be better to check if the stream is already a BufferedInputStream?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
